derivation.yuyuan_name: late 17th cent. (in the sense 'not previously described or identified scientifically'): from non- + obsolete descript 'described, engraved' (from Latin descriptus)

entry.tran: 毫无特色的;毫无吸引力的
entry.def: If you describe something or someone as nondescript, you mean that their appearance is rather dull, and not at all interesting or attractive.

example.ex: Europa House is one of those hundreds of nondescript buildings along the Bath Road.
